## Build and Test Commands

```powershell
# First run: install dependencies
.\Build\build.ps1 -ResolveDependency

# Common tasks
.\Build\build.ps1 -TaskList Test        # run Pester tests
.\Build\build.ps1 -TaskList Analyze     # lint with PSScriptAnalyzer
.\Build\build.ps1 -TaskList Help        # generate help docs
.\Build\build.ps1 -TaskList BuildNuget  # build .nupkg
```

## Architecture

```
Public/        Exported functions — one file per function, filename = function name
Private/       Internal helpers — never exported
Tests/
  Unit/        Pester 5 unit tests (*Tests.ps1)
  Common/      Shared tests (manifest, help, PSSA)
Build/         PSake tasks, dependency file, deploy script
Documentation/ Markdown help (PlatyPS)
en-US/         Compiled MAML help files
```

## Development Rules

- All paths via `Join-Path` or `$PSScriptRoot` — never concatenate or hardcode
- `[CmdletBinding()]` on every function
- Comment-based help required on all exported functions (`.SYNOPSIS`, `.DESCRIPTION`, `.PARAMETER`, `.EXAMPLE`)
- Tests in `Tests\Unit\<FunctionName>.Tests.ps1`; use Pester 5 syntax (`Should -Be`, `Should -Invoke`)
- Do not edit `.psd1` version manually; use `Update-ModuleManifest`

